# Harbor Deployment Guide

## Overview

This guide details the deployment and configuration of Harbor registry in a disconnected environment. Harbor serves as the central container registry for:
- OpenShift container images
- Custom application images
- Helm charts
- Container signing and scanning

## Prerequisites

### System Requirements
```bash
# Harbor VM Requirements
✅ CPU: 4+ cores
✅ RAM: 8GB+
✅ Storage: 500GB+ available
✅ Network: Access to both networks
   - Lab Network (192.168.50.0/24) for initial setup
   - Trans-Proxy Network (192.168.54.0/24) for disconnected operation
```

### Required Tools
```bash
# Verify tool installations
kcli --version
ansible --version
openssl version
```

## Deployment Steps

### 1. Prepare Storage
```bash
# Create Harbor data directory
sudo mkdir -p /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor
sudo chown -R $(id -u):$(id -g) /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor

# Verify storage
df -h /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor
```

### 2. Generate Certificates
```bash
# Generate Harbor certificates
./scripts/generate-harbor-certs.sh

# Verify certificate generation
ls -l /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor/certs/
```

### 3. Deploy Harbor VM
```bash
# Deploy Harbor using kcli
./scripts/deploy-harbor-vm.sh

# Monitor deployment
tail -f /var/log/libvirt/qemu/harbor.log
```

### 4. Configure Harbor
```bash
# Wait for Harbor to be ready
curl -k https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/api/v2.0/health

# Configure initial settings
./scripts/configure-harbor.sh
```

### 5. Setup Authentication
```bash
# Configure registry authentication
./scripts/pull-secret-to-harbor-auth.sh

# Join authentication configurations
./scripts/join-auths.sh

# Verify authentication
podman login ${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}
```

## Post-Deployment Configuration

### 1. Configure Projects
```bash
# Create default projects
./scripts/create-harbor-projects.sh

# Verify projects
curl -k -u "admin:${HARBOR_PASSWORD}" \
    https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/api/v2.0/projects
```

### 2. Setup Replication
```bash
# Configure replication rules
./scripts/configure-harbor-replication.sh

# Verify replication status
curl -k -u "admin:${HARBOR_PASSWORD}" \
    https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/api/v2.0/replication/executions
```

### 3. Configure Security
```bash
# Enable vulnerability scanning
./scripts/configure-harbor-security.sh

# Verify scanner status
curl -k -u "admin:${HARBOR_PASSWORD}" \
    https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/api/v2.0/scanners
```

## Verification

### 1. Test Basic Operations
```bash
# Pull test image
podman pull ubi8/ubi:latest

# Tag for Harbor
podman tag ubi8/ubi:latest ${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/library/ubi:latest

# Push to Harbor
podman push ${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/library/ubi:latest
```

### 2. Verify Registry Features
```bash
# Check image scanning
curl -k -u "admin:${HARBOR_PASSWORD}" \
    https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/api/v2.0/projects/library/repositories/ubi/artifacts/latest/scan

# Test replication
curl -k -u "admin:${HARBOR_PASSWORD}" \
    https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/api/v2.0/replication/executions
```

### 3. Validate Disconnected Operation
```bash
# Switch to disconnected network
ip route show

# Test registry access
curl -k https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/v2/
```

## Monitoring

### 1. Check System Status
```bash
# View Harbor logs
./scripts/view-harbor-logs.sh

# Check system metrics
./scripts/check-harbor-metrics.sh
```

### 2. Monitor Resources
```bash
# Check storage usage
df -h /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor

# View resource usage
top -p $(pgrep -f harbor)
```

## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

1. **Certificate Problems**
```bash
# Regenerate certificates
./scripts/generate-harbor-certs.sh --force

# Update trust store
sudo cp /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor/certs/harbor.crt \
    /etc/pki/ca-trust/source/anchors/
sudo update-ca-trust
```

2. **Authentication Issues**
```bash
# Reset admin password
./scripts/reset-harbor-admin.sh

# Clear existing credentials
rm -f ~/.docker/config.json
```

3. **Storage Problems**
```bash
# Clean up old images
./scripts/cleanup-harbor-images.sh

# Verify storage
df -h /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor
```

## Maintenance

### 1. Backup
```bash
# Backup Harbor data
./scripts/backup-harbor.sh

# Verify backup
ls -l /var/lib/libvirt/images/harbor/backups/
```

### 2. Updates
```bash
# Update Harbor components
./scripts/update-harbor.sh

# Verify update
curl -k https://${HARBOR_HOSTNAME}/api/v2.0/systeminfo
```

### 3. Health Checks
```bash
# Run health check
./scripts/check-harbor-health.sh

# View results
cat /var/log/harbor/health-check.log
```

## Security Considerations

1. **Access Control**
   - Use RBAC for project access
   - Enable content trust for image signing
   - Configure vulnerability scanning policies

2. **Network Security**
   - Restrict access to Harbor endpoints
   - Use TLS for all connections
   - Configure firewall rules

3. **Monitoring**
   - Enable audit logging
   - Monitor system resources
   - Track failed login attempts

